{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Amend TUA 2016, so non-union members pay for benefits gained from Union work.",
        "additional_details": "Union members already make financial contribution to support their union to act on their behalf however non-members receive the benefit of this rise without having made any financial contribution to the costs of the union achieving this mutually beneficially outcome.\r\nMake non-union members pay monthly contribution, not exceeding subs paid by union members or they will receive only the 1% payrise.",
        "background": "Benefits negotiated by Trade unions at the workplace are enjoyed by union members & non-members alike.\r\ne.g. Workplace offers 1% pay rise to workforce but through negotiations with trade union, an increased offer of 2.5% is agreed. Members & non-members alike are given a 2.5% pay rise as a result.",
